        "text": "Cheltenham-based law firm BPE Solicitors has acted for HiETA Technologies Limited on a recent significant investment from Dorset-baed Meggitt(UK) Ltd.\n\nHiETA Technologies has been providing the automotive, aerospace, defence, energy and motorsports industries with products and services using additive manufacturing techniques since 2011. The Bristol-based company has decades of experience through itsfounders and focuses on heat exchanging and recovery technology, particularly in engines.\n\nMeggitt (UK) Ltd is a subsidiary of Meggitt PLC, a global business specialising in advanced products and technology for the aviation, defence and energy sectors.\n\nThe investment from Meggitt (UK) Ltd will enable HiETA Technologies to accelerate the development of the next line of thermal technology systems. These systems are key for HiETA as they will enable the continued development of sustainable aviation and low carbon power generation solutions.\n\nLed by Senior Associate Adam Kean and supported by Angharad Doyle, Philippa Kean and Rupert Parker, BPE’s Corporate Team was assisted by the firm’s IT and Cyber Team, overseeing both the investment transaction and relevant technical contracts.\n\nAdam commented: “We are delighted to have supported HiETA and the founders in securing this key investment into the company to help grow the business and build on its successful trading history.”\n\nHiETA Technologies’ CEO and co-founder, Mike Adams said: “We are delighted to have secured the investment from a leading international company in high performance components and subsystems for the aerospace, defence and selected energy markets, bringing an incredible wealth of experience to HiETA.”"
